headline: 7 Dow Jones Dividend Stocks that Underperformed the S&P 500 This Year but Are Buys for 2025
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average is chock-full of industry-leading blue chip stocks -- many of which pay dividends.  Investors looking for established companies with track records for earnings growth have come to the right place.  Here's why Visa (NYSE: V), Microsoft (NASDAQ: MSFT), Procter & Gamble (NYSE: PG), Coca-Cola (NYSE: KO), McDonald's (NYSE: MCD), Chevron (NYSE: CVX), and Nike (NYSE: NKE) are seven excellent Dow stocks that have underperformed the S&P 500 in 2024 but stand out as great buys for 2025.
